                    <span>This is an excellent presentation for students of formal
<br />public speaking. It covers model speakers, target audiences,
<br />content, gestures and many of the fine nuances that professional
<br />speakers utilize in making presentations before audiences.
<br />The authors even cover insensitivities and proper protocol
<br />for public speakers. The book is a worthy investment for
<br />business people, a large constituency of students, teachers,
<br />collegiate administrators and public policy makers.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Best in its field!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
